==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infatuation
<hw>In*fat`u*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>infatuatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>infatuation</ets>.]</ety> <def>The
act of infatuating; the state of being infatuated; folly; that which
infatuates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>infatuations</qex> of the sensual and frivolous part of
mankind are amazing; but the <qex>infatuations</qex> of the learned and
sophistical are incomparably more so.</q> <rj><qau>I.
Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such is the <qex>infatuation</qex> of self-love.</q>
<rj><qau>Blair.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infaust</ent>⟦br⟧
